Package com.steelypip.powerups.alert

Class Alert

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • java.lang.RuntimeException
          • com.steelypip.powerups.alert.Alert
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<Culprit>
    public class Alert
extends RuntimeException
implements Iterable<Culprit>
    Alerts are intended to act as generic application exceptions that can be decorated with contextual key-value information. The idiom for using them is: throw new Alert( message ).culprit( key1, value1 ).culprit( key2, value2 ); As the exception propogates outward, it is appropriate for additional information to be tagged onto the exception and for it to be re-thrown.
